<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Quercus sadleriana </i>vigorously sprouts from a root crown after fire. While fire information for this alliance is not well known, it is probably similar to <i>Q. vacciniifolia </i>in that it acts as a ladder fuel in conifer stands and regenerates quickly after fires in clear cuts. <i>Q. sadleriana </i>may dominate for 10-50 years until conifer species establish and overtop the shrubs. Some <i>Q. sadleriana </i>stands persist on steep, open rocky sites.</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (25-75+ years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Seasonality</td>
			<td>Summer-early fall
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Size/extent</td>
			<td>Medium to large—up to and beyond stand
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Complexity</td>
			<td>Low to moderate
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
