    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Klamath Mountains</b> (M261Aa, Ad, Af-g, An-r, At). Stands are restricted to the western and central Klamath at mid elevations. The stand at Indian Creek Brewer Spruce dRNA (Sawyer et al. 1978b, see Cheng 2004) is one of the most accessible Others occur in Marble, Salmon, and Siskiyou mountains, and Trinity Alps (Calveg 2005).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> This is largely a seral alliance; species composition and stand size varies with disturbance history. Stands are frequent in areas with a history of logging. </div>
</div>

    

    

